<html> 
<head> 
<title>Perspectives on DARE (The Lindesmith Center)</title> 
</head> 
 
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF" link="006699" vlink="339999" text="000000">
<center><h4>THE 
LINDESMITH CENTER</h4></center> 
<center><img align=middle src=line.gif width=600 alt=#></center><p> 
Critical analyses of DARE available on this site include: 
<ul> 
<li> 
"<a 
href="tlcbrow.html">In Their Own Voices</a>," a report by the Pacific Institute for Research and 
Evaluation for the California State Board of Education.
<li><a href="tlctaos.html">Report of the 
Committee to Review the Tobacco, Alcohol and Other Substances (TAOS) Curriculum</a>. 
<li>Jeff Elliot's article from the March, 1995 <i>Reason</i>, "<a href="tlcdare.html">Drug Prevention 
Placebo: How DARE Wastes Time, Money, and 
Police</a>."</h3> 
<p>
<hr> 
<p> 
<center>
