<head> 
<title> Peregrine to scale back in Burma 
</title> 
</head> 
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF"> 
 <center><h1>
Peregrine to scale back in Burma
</h1></center> 
     
Peregrine Investments Holdings decided to scale back its operations in
   Burma, following the authorities' refusal to renew the visas of the
firm's top
   executives in the country. The move came shortly after Peregrine won a
   $4.1 million suit against its former Burma chairman, Miriam Marshall Segal, 
   a veteran of business in Burma who is well-connected with the country's 
   military rulers.
<p>
