<head>      
<title> Singapore firm to invest in Myanmar's agriculture
</title>      
</head>      
<body bgcolor="FFFFFF">      
<table border=0 cellpadding=6>      
<tr>      
<td><h1>      
Singapore firm to invest in Myanmar's agriculture
</h1></td>      
</table>      

December 4, 1996, <p>

    A Singaporean company has signed a contract with the state-run 
     Myanmar farms enterprise making investment in agriculture in Myanmar.  the company 
     --Kee Aun (tong san) pte ltd. is to reclaim low-lying areas in Pantanaw 
     township, cultivate high quality paddy and establish a rice mill for milling and 
     marketing under the contract signed here tuesday, the official paper the new 
     light of Myanmar reported today.  Since Myanmar opened its doors to foreign 
     investment, there had been only one project in agriculture with an investment of 
     2.69 million US dollars by the end of October this year, according to the 
     official statistics.  More investment in this sector, both local and foreign, 
     is being encouraged for Myanmar is rich in agricultural land resources and 
     agricultural labor is relatively cheap.
<p>
Xinhua News Agency<br>
